OL,10,GTactile paving (those bobbly bits of
OL,11,Gpavements you find around crossings)
OL,12,Ghas been with us since the 90s and is
OL,13,Gnow ubiquitous, but it's not working
OL,14,Gas well as it should for the blind and
OL,15,Gpartially sighted people who need it.
OL,16,GIts use is controlled by a government
OL,17,Gguidance document but this is not
OL,18,Glegally binding and it does not cover
OL,19,Glots of features that are now common
OL,20,Gon our streets. This leads to
OL,22,D]CEMFFAX: The world at your fingertips\
